(74, 'Hidden Hazards: Understanding the Long-Term Risks of Untreated Wisdom Teeth', NULL, '<p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Wisdom teeth, also known as third molars, often do not erupt properly and become impacted. When left unaddressed, impacted wisdom teeth can lead to several long-term oral health complications. Identifying these issues early and consulting specialists at Vision Multispeciality Dental Hospital, recognized as the </span><u style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(17, 85, 204);\"><a href=\"https://visiondentalguntur.com/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">best dental hospital in Guntur</a></u><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">, can help you avoid serious problems down the road.</span></p>', NULL, '<h3><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(255, 0, 0);\">Persistent Pain and Oral Discomfort</strong></h3><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Impacted wisdom teeth often lead to:</span></p><ol><li data-list=\"bullet\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Constant pain in the jaw</span></li><li data-list=\"bullet\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span><br></li><li data-list=\"bullet\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Difficulty in chewing and speaking</span></li><li data-list=\"bullet\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span><br></li><li data-list=\"bullet\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Inflammation and tenderness in the rear of the oral cavity</span></li><li data-list=\"bullet\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span><br></li></ol><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Over time, these symptoms can intensify, affecting your ability to eat, sleep, or concentrate. </span><u style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(17, 85, 204);\"><a href=\"https://visiondentalguntur.com/about.php\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Dr. Abhilash</a></u><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">, one of the most trusted and experienced dental surgeons at Vision Multispeciality Dental Hospital, advises early evaluation to maintain long-term comfort.</span></p><h3><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(255, 0, 0);\">Increased Risk of Infection</strong></h3><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Due to limited space and difficult positioning, impacted wisdom teeth trap food and bacteria, leading to:</span></p><ol><li data-list=\"bullet\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Pericoronitis</span><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"> – </strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">a condition marked by inflamed gums near an emerging wisdom tooth</span></li><li data-list=\"bullet\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span><br></li><li data-list=\"bullet\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Abscess formation with pus buildup</span></li><li data-list=\"bullet\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span><br></li><li data-list=\"bullet\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Spread of infection beyond the mouth in severe cases</span></li></ol><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Prompt </span><u style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(17, 85, 204);\"><a href=\"https://visiondentalguntur.com/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">wisdom tooth removal </a></u><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">by experts like </span><u style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(17, 85, 204);\"><a href=\"https://visiondentalguntur.com/about.php\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Dr. Latha Sree</a></u><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">, a skilled dental professional at Vision Multispeciality Dental Hospital, can help prevent these infections before they escalate.</span></p><h3><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(255, 0, 0);\">Harm to Adjacent Teeth</strong></h3><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">When wisdom teeth grow at improper angles, they can press against nearby molars, causing:</span></p><ol><li data-list=\"bullet\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Shifting or crowding of other teeth</span></li><li data-list=\"bullet\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span><br></li><li data-list=\"bullet\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Tooth decay in hard-to-clean areas</span></li><li data-list=\"bullet\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span><br></li><li data-list=\"bullet\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Root resorption or weakening of adjacent teeth</span></li></ol><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Patients often experience relief after undergoing safe and precise wisdom tooth removal under the care of Dr. Abhilash and his team in Guntur.</span></p><h3><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(255, 0, 0);\">Orthodontic Setbacks</strong></h3><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">For individuals who have previously worn braces, wisdom teeth can undo that alignment by:</span></p><ol><li data-list=\"bullet\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Crowding front teeth</span></li><li data-list=\"bullet\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span><br></li><li data-list=\"bullet\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Disrupting the bite pattern</span></li><li data-list=\"bullet\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span><br></li><li data-list=\"bullet\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Requiring renewed orthodontic treatments</span></li><li data-list=\"bullet\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span><br></li></ol><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Routine dental checkups at Vision Multispeciality Dental Hospital can help detect such issues early and protect your smile.</span></p><h3><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(255, 0, 0);\">Rare but Serious Growths</strong></h3><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Wisdom teeth that are not treated can, in infrequent cases, lead to:</span></p><ol><li data-list=\"bullet\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Fluid-filled dentigerous cysts</span></li><li data-list=\"bullet\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span><br></li><li data-list=\"bullet\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Non-cancerous odontogenic tumors</span></li></ol><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">These conditions can cause severe bone loss and may need complex surgical care. Vision Multispeciality Dental Hospital in Guntur is well-equipped to handle such advanced treatments safely.</span></p><h3><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(255, 0, 0);\">Final Thoughts</strong></h3><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Even if impacted wisdom teeth don’t always demand urgent removal, periodic checkups are vital. A personalized evaluation by experienced professionals like Dr. Abhilash or Dr. Latha Sree ensures that any developing issues are addressed on time.</span></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">For safe, effective, and expert-guided wisdom tooth removal, trust the specialists at </span><u style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(17, 85, 204);\"><a href=\"https://www.google.com/maps/place/Vision+MultiSpeciality+Dental+Hospital+Guntur+%7C+Best+Dentist+in+Guntur/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x0:0xc24e52047b5202de?sa=X&amp;ved=1t:2428&amp;hl=en-GB&amp;ictx=111\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Vision Multispeciality Dental Hospital</a></u><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 255);\">,</span><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"> proudly recognized as the best dental hospital in Guntur. Whether you need advice, diagnosis, or treatment, the combined expertise of Dr. Abhilash and Dr. Latha Sree ensures you receive the highest quality dental care from the </span><u style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(17, 85, 204);\"><a href=\"https://www.google.com/maps/place/Vision+MultiSpeciality+Dental+Hospital+Guntur+%7C+Best+Dentist+in+Guntur/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x0:0xc24e52047b5202de?sa=X&amp;ved=1t:2428&amp;hl=en-GB&amp;ictx=111\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">best dentist in Guntur.</a></u></p><p><br></p>', NULL, '', '684d53d426b35_1749898196.jpg', '684d53d426bf1_1749898196.mp4', 'Jaw Corrective', '2025-06-14 10:43:29', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(75, '5 Essential Facts About Baby Teeth Every Parent Should Know', NULL, '<p>As a parent, you have a lot to think about when it comes to your child\'s health and development. One area that’s often overlooked, but equally important, is dental care—especially when it comes to baby teeth. While these early teeth may seem temporary, they play a crucial role in your child\'s overall health and well-being.</p><p><br></p>', NULL, '<p><br></p><p>At Vision Multispeciality Dental Hospital in Guntur, we’re committed to helping parents understand the significance of baby teeth and providing the Best Dental care for children in guntur from the start. Here are five key facts every parent should know about baby teeth:</p><p><br></p><p><strong>1. Baby Teeth Are More Important Than You Think</strong></p><p><br></p><p>It’s common to assume that baby teeth don’t matter because they’ll eventually fall out. However, they are far more important than most people realise. Baby teeth help your child chew, speak, and form proper mouth habits. They also guide the permanent teeth into their correct positions. Healthy baby teeth are essential for preventing alignment issues, overcrowding, or even speech problems in the future. Taking care of these early teeth sets the foundation for lifelong oral health.</p><p><br></p><p><strong>2. When Will Baby Teeth Erupt?</strong></p><p><br></p><p>Baby teeth typically start coming in between the ages of 6 months and 1 year, though the timing can vary from child to child. By age 3, most children will have a full set of 20 primary teeth. It’s important to remember that every child is different, so don’t be alarmed if your child’s teeth arrive a little earlier or later than expected. If you notice significant delays or other concerns with your child’s teething process, it’s always a good idea to consult with a paediatric dentist at Vision Multispeciality Dental Hospital to ensure everything is on track.</p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><strong>3. Start Dental Hygiene Early</strong></p><p><br></p><p>Establishing a dental care routine early can help set your child up for a lifetime of healthy teeth. Even before your baby’s first tooth appears, you can clean their gums with a soft, damp cloth after feeding. Once the first tooth emerges, use a soft-bristled toothbrush and a small amount of fluoride toothpaste. Developing good habits early—like brushing twice a day—will teach your child the importance of oral hygiene and help prevent future dental issues.</p><p><br></p><p><strong>4. Baby Teeth Can Get Cavities Too</strong></p><p><br></p><p>Just because baby teeth will eventually fall out doesn’t mean they’re immune to cavities. In fact, untreated cavities in baby teeth can lead to pain, infection, and even issues with the development of adult teeth. A common cause of early tooth decay is baby bottle tooth decay, which happens when sugary liquids like milk or juice pool in the mouth during naps or bedtime. To avoid cavities, avoid letting your child fall asleep with a bottle of milk or juice, and try cleaning their teeth or gums after feeding. Regular dental visits starting at around age 1 will help monitor your child’s dental health and catch any issues early.</p><p><br></p><p><strong>5. Losing Baby Teeth Is a Natural Process</strong></p><p><br></p><p>Around age 6, children begin to lose their baby teeth to make way for adult teeth. This milestone is often an exciting and memorable event for both children and parents—especially when the Tooth Fairy comes to visit! However, some children may feel anxious or scared about losing their teeth. It’s important to reassure them that this is a normal and healthy part of growing up, and that their adult teeth will be even stronger and permanent. At Vision Multispeciality Dental Hospital, we’re here to help guide you and your child through this process, answering any questions along the way. </p><p><br></p><p>Why Early Dental Care Matters</p><p><br></p><p>Taking care of your child’s baby teeth is just as important as caring for their adult teeth. By understanding the role of baby teeth, knowing when to expect teething, establishing good dental habits early, preventing cavities, and preparing for tooth loss, you’ll be well on your way to supporting your child’s dental health.</p><p><br></p><p>At Vision Multispeciality Dental Hospital in Guntur, we’re dedicated to providing exceptional care for your child’s teeth from their very first visit. Our experienced paediatric dental team is here to ensure your child’s smile stays bright and healthy through every stage of their development.</p><p><br></p><p>If you’re looking for Best children dental clinic in Guntur, Vision Multispeciality Dental Hospital is here to help. Our team is ready to guide you through every step of your child’s dental journey, from teething to regular checkups to the transition to adult teeth.</p><p><br></p><p> </p><p><br></p><p>Schedule Your Child’s Dental Appointment Today</p><p><br></p><p>Don’t wait to take care of your child’s dental health. Contact us today to schedule an appointment and ensure their smile stays healthy for years to come.</p><p><br></p><p>At Vision Multispeciality Dental Hospital, we’re here to make dental care a positive experience for both you&nbsp;and&nbsp;your&nbsp;child!</p>', NULL, '', '684d53174d8a9_1749898007.png', '684d53174da39_1749898007.mp4', 'Pediatric Dentist', '2025-06-14 10:46:47', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(76, '7 Advantages of Professional Teeth Whitening Treatments', NULL, '<h1 class=\"ql-align-center\"><br></h1><p><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent;\">A radiant smile is universally seen as a sign of confidence and charm. However, as time passes, factors like aging, dietary habits, smoking, and certain medications can lead to stained or discolored teeth, diminishing the appeal of your smile. While over-the-counter whitening products exist, professional teeth whitening treatments offer clear advantages in terms of safety, effectiveness, and long-term results.</span></p>', NULL, '<p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">At Vision Multispeciality Dental Hospital, recognized as the</span><u style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(17, 85, 204);\"><a href=\"https://visiondentalguntur.com/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\"> best dental hospital in Guntur</a></u><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">, professional teeth whitening services are provided by experienced specialists </span><u style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(17, 85, 204);\"><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/visiondentalguntur/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Dr. Abhilash</a></u><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"> and </span><u style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(17, 85, 204);\"><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/visiondentalguntur/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Dr. Lathasree</a></u><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">. Here are seven major advantages of opting for their professional teeth whitening treatment:</span></p><h3><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">1. Drastic Results</strong></h3><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">One of the most significant benefits of choosing professional teeth whitening 